CatDescriptText: Cutline of image published in Flash Newspicture Magazine, April 19, 1938, pg. unknown, reads: "Fashionable Loendi Club, rendezvous of Pittsburgh's social minded Firsts presents these two prominent gentlemen, Attorney Joseph Givens, big-wig of the Club's social committee, and Amos Galloway, the oldest members of the Loendi Club. This spot is the mother-link of 'Smoketown's' inimitable Frogs. (Photos by 'Teenie' Harris)."
TitMainTitle: Amos Galloway and Atty. Joseph Givens posed in Loendi Club
